<s> [INST] You are an expert in Natural Language Inference (NLI). Please list all possible explanations why the the following statement is true (entailment) given the context below without introductory phrases. 
Context: When he's ready for a major strike, how many innocents do you suppose are going to suffer? To quote one of your contemporaries; 'The needs of the many outweigh the needs of the few.' ' 
Statement: He won't care how many innocent people will suffer. 
Answer: [/INST] 1. The person in question prioritizes the overall goal (the "many") over the individual victims (the "few").
2. The person is willing to inflict harm on innocent people for the sake of achieving their objective.
3. The person is ruthless and unsympathetic towards the suffering of others.
4. The person values the success of the mission more than the well-being of innocent bystanders.
5. The person is not deterred by the potential harm to innocents, as they believe it is justified for the greater good.
6. The person is not concerned about the consequences of their actions on innocent people.
7. The person is willing to make sacrifices, even if it means innocent people will suffer.
8. The person is unswayed by the emotional impact of causing suffering to innocents.
9. The person is focused on their objective and is indifferent to the collateral damage.
10. The person is convinced that the end justifies the means, even if it results in innocent casualties.</s>